[{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q01","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":1,"marks":2,"topics":["Number","Mensuration"],"s":"1.3","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Powers and roots","qtype":"powers and roots","g":"indices","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q01","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"From the list of numbers, write down\n\\[\n    61, \\quad 62, \\quad 63, \\quad 64, \\quad 65, \\quad 66, \\quad 67, \\quad 68, \\quad 69\n\\]\n\n(a) a cube number\n\n    \n\n(b) a prime number.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"write"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q02","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":2,"marks":1,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q02","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"A train journey starts at 23 30 and finishes at 07 15 the next day.\n\nFind the time taken for this journey.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find","answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"h \\dots min"}},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q03","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":3,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q03","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Simplify.\n\n\\[3p - t - p - 4t\\]","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q04","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":4,"marks":3,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.3","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Scale drawings and bearings","qtype":"scale drawings and bearings","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q04","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The scale drawing shows the positions of town $K$ and town $L$. \\\\\nThe scale is 1 cm represents 10 km.\n\n(a) Find the actual distance between town $K$ and town $L$.\n\n    \n\n(b) Measure the bearing of town $L$ from town $K$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2,"answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"km"}},{"label":"(b)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q05","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":5,"marks":4,"topics":["Statistics"],"s":"9.3","d":2,"cat":"statistics","topic":"Averages and measures of spread","qtype":"averages and spread","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q05","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Each student in a class of 20 students records the number of coins in their pockets. \\\\\nThe table shows the results.\n\\begin{tabular}{|l|c|c|c|c|c|c|c|}\n\\hline\nNumber of coins & 0 & 1 & 2 & 3 & 4 & 5 & 6 \\\\ \\hline\nFrequency       & 3 & 1 & 7 & 8 & 0 & 0 & 1 \\\\ \\hline\n\\end{tabular}\n(a) Find the median.\n\n    \n\n(b) Calculate the mean.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":3}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate","texHtml":"Each student in a class of 20 students records the number of coins in their pockets. \\\\\nThe table shows the results.\n<div class=\"pp-table-wrap\"><table class=\"pp-table\"><tr><th>Number of coins</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">0</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">1</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">2</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">3</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">4</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">5</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">6</th></tr><tr><td>Frequency</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">3</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">1</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">7</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">8</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">0</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">0</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">1</td></tr></table></div>\n(a) Find the median.\n\n    \n\n(b) Calculate the mean."},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q06","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":6,"marks":1,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q06","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The diagram shows three lines meeting at a point.\n\nFind the value of $w$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find","answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"w = \\dots"}},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q07","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":7,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q07","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Solve the equation.\n\\[\n    7 - h = 3 - 5h\n\\]","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve","answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"h = \\dots"}},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q08","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":8,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q08","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Sacha buys $b$ books and $m$ magazines. \\\\\nThe cost of each book is \\$12 and the cost of each magazine is \\$5.\n\nWrite an expression, in terms of $b$ and $m$, for the total cost of the books and the magazines.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"write"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q09","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":9,"marks":2,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.6","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q09","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Find the size of an interior angle of a regular 15-sided polygon.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q10","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":10,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.4","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q10","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Without using a calculator, work out $2\\frac{1}{4} - 1\\frac{11}{12}$. \\\\\nYou must show all your working and give your answer as a fraction in its simplest form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q11","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":11,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.5","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Equations","qtype":"equations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q11","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Solve the simultaneous equations.\n\\begin{align*}\n    3p - 2q &= 7 \\\\\n    p + 2q &= 1\n\\end{align*}","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve","answer":{"type":"multiline","lines":2,"layout":"column","template":"____ p = \\dots\\n____ q = \\dots"}},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q12","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":12,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.5","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Equations","qtype":"equations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q12","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"\\[\n    V = \\frac{3x}{y}\n\\]\nRearrange the formula to write $x$ in terms of $V$ and $y$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"rearrange","answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"x = \\dots"}},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q13","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":13,"marks":4,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.7","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Sequences","qtype":"sequences","g":"sequence","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q13","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Find the $n$th term of each sequence.\n\n(a) \n\n    $21, \\quad 13, \\quad 5, \\quad -3, \\quad -11, \\quad \\dots$\n\n    \n\n(b) \n\n    $2.5, \\quad 5, \\quad 10, \\quad 20, \\quad 40, \\quad \\dots$","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q14","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":14,"marks":4,"topics":["Geometry","Trigonometry"],"s":"4.7","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Circle theorems","qtype":"circle theorems","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q14","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"(a) \n\n    $A, B, C$ and $D$ lie on the circle. \\\\\n    $TAS$ is a tangent to the circle at $A$.\n\n    \\begin{parts}\n\n(b) Find the value of $x$.\n\n        \n\n(c) Find the value of $y$.\n\n        \n\n\n\n    $P, Q$ and $R$ lie on the circle, centre $O$. \\\\\n    Find the value of $w$.\n\n    \n\\end{parts}","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":0},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":1},{"label":"(d)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q15","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":15,"marks":2,"topics":["Statistics"],"s":"9.6","d":2,"cat":"statistics","topic":"Cumulative frequency","qtype":"cumulative frequency","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q15","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The box-and-whisker diagram shows information about the heights of some plants.\n\n(a) Find the median height.\n\n    \n\n(b) Find the interquartile range of the heights.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1,"answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"cm"}},{"label":"(b)","marks":1,"answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"cm"}}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q16","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":16,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q16","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Calculate the shortest distance from $C$ to $AB$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate","answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"cm"}},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q17","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":17,"marks":4,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q17","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Simplify.\n\n(a) $18x^{18} \\div 3x^3$\n\n    \n\n(b) $(125y^{75})^{\\frac{2}{3}}$","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q18","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":18,"marks":3,"topics":["Geometry","Mensuration"],"s":"4.4","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Similarity and congruence","qtype":"similarity and congruence","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q18","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Two mathematically similar solids have volumes 81 cm$^3$ and 24 cm$^3$. \\\\\nThe height of the smaller solid is 4.8 cm.\n\nCalculate the height of the larger solid.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate","answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"cm"}},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q19","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":19,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.8","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Proportion","qtype":"proportion","g":"proportion","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q19","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"$y$ is inversely proportional to $x + 2$. \\\\\nWhen $x = 2$, $y = 3$.\n\nFind $y$ in terms of $x$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find","answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"y = \\dots"}},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q20","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":20,"marks":3,"topics":["Trigonometry"],"s":"6.4","d":2,"cat":"trigonometry","topic":"Trigonometric functions","qtype":"solving trigonometric equations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q20","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Solve the equation $\\tan x + 2 = 0$ for $0^\\circ \\leqslant x \\leqslant 360^\\circ$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve","answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"x = \\dots or x = \\dots"}},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper23-Q21","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper23","qnum":21,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.2","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Sets","qtype":"sets and Venn diagrams","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/24 Q21","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The Venn diagram shows the number of elements in each region.\n\n(a)